WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.992 align:middle line:90%


00:00:00.992 --> 00:00:05.456 align:middle line:90%
[TRIBAL MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:05.456 --> 00:01:05.968 align:middle line:90%


00:01:05.968 --> 00:01:09.800 align:middle line:84%
>> This is the biggest
rock in the world.

00:01:09.800 --> 00:01:12.493 align:middle line:84%
It was modeled out of
mud by two small boys who

00:01:12.493 --> 00:01:13.660 align:middle line:90%
were playing after rainfall.

00:01:13.660 --> 00:01:16.900 align:middle line:90%


00:01:16.900 --> 00:01:20.700 align:middle line:90%
It was in the Dreamtime.

00:01:20.700 --> 00:01:22.710 align:middle line:84%
Is how the Aborigines
explain the presence

00:01:22.710 --> 00:01:25.050 align:middle line:84%
of this enormous massive
sandstone in the middle

00:01:25.050 --> 00:01:26.230 align:middle line:90%
of the Australian desert.

00:01:26.230 --> 00:01:32.922 align:middle line:90%


00:01:32.922 --> 00:01:37.220 align:middle line:84%
>> Its original name is Uluru,
but it's more often known

00:01:37.220 --> 00:01:38.080 align:middle line:90%
as Ayers Rock.

00:01:38.080 --> 00:01:42.740 align:middle line:90%


00:01:42.740 --> 00:01:46.370 align:middle line:84%
Ayers Rock is three and 1/2
kilometers long by two and 1/2

00:01:46.370 --> 00:01:47.510 align:middle line:90%
wide.

00:01:47.510 --> 00:01:49.950 align:middle line:84%
It looms 350 meters
above the plain.

00:01:49.950 --> 00:01:58.297 align:middle line:90%


00:01:58.297 --> 00:02:02.210 align:middle line:84%
>> For 600 million years, its
old carcass has been attacked

00:02:02.210 --> 00:02:06.935 align:middle line:84%
by the sun, the
rain, and the wind.

00:02:06.935 --> 00:02:10.400 align:middle line:90%


00:02:10.400 --> 00:02:12.290 align:middle line:10%
But we can also
see on its slopes

00:02:12.290 --> 00:02:14.450 align:middle line:10%
the traces left
behind by the battles

00:02:14.450 --> 00:02:17.180 align:middle line:10%
between two mythical
heroes, the snake spirits.

00:02:17.180 --> 00:02:26.779 align:middle line:90%


00:02:26.779 --> 00:02:31.070 align:middle line:84%
>> To the west of the monolith
rise the 36 domes of the Olga

00:02:31.070 --> 00:02:31.870 align:middle line:90%
Mountains.

00:02:31.870 --> 00:02:37.200 align:middle line:90%


00:02:37.200 --> 00:02:40.500 align:middle line:84%
For the Anangu people,
this is Kata Tjuta,

00:02:40.500 --> 00:02:43.620 align:middle line:84%
which literally means,
many heads, a reference

00:02:43.620 --> 00:02:45.546 align:middle line:90%
to the shape of the rocks.

00:02:45.546 --> 00:02:49.920 align:middle line:90%
[TRIBAL MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:49.920 --> 00:02:55.266 align:middle line:90%


00:02:55.266 --> 00:02:58.520 align:middle line:84%
>> The Anangus have been living
in this region for at least

00:02:58.520 --> 00:03:01.250 align:middle line:90%
20,000 years.

00:03:01.250 --> 00:03:04.670 align:middle line:84%
For them, Uluru and Kata
Tjuta are sacred places.

00:03:04.670 --> 00:03:12.350 align:middle line:90%


00:03:12.350 --> 00:03:14.690 align:middle line:84%
The two sides have the
same spiritual importance

00:03:14.690 --> 00:03:16.260 align:middle line:90%
for the Aborigines.

00:03:16.260 --> 00:03:18.725 align:middle line:84%
But the rocks of Kata
Tjuta are the most secret.

00:03:18.725 --> 00:03:21.530 align:middle line:90%


00:03:21.530 --> 00:03:23.660 align:middle line:84%
The myths and beliefs
linked to them

00:03:23.660 --> 00:03:25.070 align:middle line:90%
are only for the initiated.

00:03:25.070 --> 00:03:35.894 align:middle line:90%


00:03:35.894 --> 00:03:40.620 align:middle line:84%
>> Less than 300 kilometers away
to the east stands a monolith

00:03:40.620 --> 00:03:41.700 align:middle line:90%
50 meters high.

00:03:41.700 --> 00:03:45.750 align:middle line:90%


00:03:45.750 --> 00:03:49.700 align:middle line:90%
It's called Chambers Pillar.

00:03:49.700 --> 00:03:52.220 align:middle line:84%
Like Ayers Rock and
the Olga Mountains,

00:03:52.220 --> 00:03:55.930 align:middle line:90%
it's a block of sandstone.

00:03:55.930 --> 00:03:58.890 align:middle line:84%
Its spectacular mass was
uncovered by erosion.

00:03:58.890 --> 00:04:04.253 align:middle line:90%


00:04:04.253 --> 00:04:07.180 align:middle line:84%
>> Chambers Pillar was only
discovered by explorers

00:04:07.180 --> 00:04:09.740 align:middle line:90%
in 1860.

00:04:09.740 --> 00:04:11.950 align:middle line:90%
It became a landmark.

00:04:11.950 --> 00:04:14.080 align:middle line:84%
But the Aborigines
had always known it.

00:04:14.080 --> 00:04:19.730 align:middle line:90%


00:04:19.730 --> 00:04:22.520 align:middle line:90%
For them, it is a sacred rock.

00:04:22.520 --> 00:04:26.312 align:middle line:84%
They see in it the petrified
form of Itirkawara.

00:04:26.312 --> 00:04:30.890 align:middle line:84%
>> Itirkawara is a character
from their founding myth,

00:04:30.890 --> 00:04:33.290 align:middle line:84%
a gecko who turned
himself into a giant.

00:04:33.290 --> 00:04:36.270 align:middle line:90%


00:04:36.270 --> 00:04:39.840 align:middle line:84%
In the Dreamtime, he is supposed
to have fallen asleep here

00:04:39.840 --> 00:04:40.980 align:middle line:90%
and turned into a rock.

00:04:40.980 --> 00:04:45.770 align:middle line:90%


00:04:45.770 --> 00:04:48.980 align:middle line:84%
>> If you go 500
kilometers north of here,

00:04:48.980 --> 00:04:51.230 align:middle line:84%
you will find another
natural curiosity.

00:04:51.230 --> 00:04:54.380 align:middle line:90%
[DIDGERIDOO BLOWING]

00:04:54.380 --> 00:04:58.780 align:middle line:84%
Huge spherical rocks
made of red granite.

00:04:58.780 --> 00:05:00.400 align:middle line:90%
These are the Devils Marbles.

00:05:00.400 --> 00:05:10.620 align:middle line:90%


00:05:10.620 --> 00:05:14.390 align:middle line:84%
>> For scientists, these rocks
were formed by the compression

00:05:14.390 --> 00:05:16.445 align:middle line:84%
of lava within
the Earth's crust.

00:05:16.445 --> 00:05:20.280 align:middle line:90%


00:05:20.280 --> 00:05:23.250 align:middle line:84%
For the Aborigines, these
balls were left there

00:05:23.250 --> 00:05:24.255 align:middle line:90%
by the Rainbow Snake.

00:05:24.255 --> 00:05:26.850 align:middle line:90%


00:05:26.850 --> 00:05:29.480 align:middle line:84%
Once again, this was
in the Dreamtime.

00:05:29.480 --> 00:05:36.200 align:middle line:90%


00:05:36.200 --> 00:05:40.330 align:middle line:84%
>> The Dreamtime is the basic
concept of Aboriginal belief.

00:05:40.330 --> 00:05:44.210 align:middle line:90%


00:05:44.210 --> 00:05:46.695 align:middle line:84%
We can see it illustrated in
these petroglyphs in N'Dhala

00:05:46.695 --> 00:05:47.495 align:middle line:90%
Gorge.

00:05:47.495 --> 00:05:50.360 align:middle line:90%


00:05:50.360 --> 00:05:53.870 align:middle line:84%
It was the earliest
time, an imaginary time

00:05:53.870 --> 00:05:55.190 align:middle line:90%
when spirits roamed the land.

00:05:55.190 --> 00:05:58.580 align:middle line:90%


00:05:58.580 --> 00:06:04.710 align:middle line:84%
They created landscapes,
men, animals, forests, lakes.

00:06:04.710 --> 00:06:07.230 align:middle line:84%
But at the same time they
created the language,

00:06:07.230 --> 00:06:09.480 align:middle line:84%
the rules, and the
laws of their tribe.

00:06:09.480 --> 00:06:17.400 align:middle line:90%


00:06:17.400 --> 00:06:22.010 align:middle line:10%
>> For the Aborigines,
all this is one--

00:06:22.010 --> 00:06:26.030 align:middle line:10%
the trees, the rocks,
the birds, the men,

00:06:26.030 --> 00:06:28.605 align:middle line:10%
are the inseparable
components of one creation.

00:06:28.605 --> 00:06:34.738 align:middle line:90%


00:06:34.738 --> 00:06:38.310 align:middle line:84%
>> This global fashion of
perceiving the world is without

00:06:38.310 --> 00:06:44.080 align:middle line:84%
doubt the most ancient spiritual
way that man has explored.

00:06:44.080 --> 00:06:46.960 align:middle line:84%
It persists where nature's
influence weighs most heavily

00:06:46.960 --> 00:06:53.134 align:middle line:84%
in everyday life, where a man
feels intimately bound to it.

00:06:53.134 --> 00:06:58.350 align:middle line:90%


00:06:58.350 --> 00:07:00.630 align:middle line:84%
This fosters a mixture
of magic and religion

00:07:00.630 --> 00:07:04.620 align:middle line:84%
known as shamanism, still very
much alive among the Mongols.

00:07:04.620 --> 00:07:16.752 align:middle line:90%


00:07:16.752 --> 00:07:20.290 align:middle line:84%
>> The daily concern of
these nomadic tribes is

00:07:20.290 --> 00:07:23.360 align:middle line:90%
the well-being of their herds.

00:07:23.360 --> 00:07:27.090 align:middle line:84%
They raise long
legs and short legs.

00:07:27.090 --> 00:07:30.230 align:middle line:84%
The short legs are the cows
and ewes because they never

00:07:30.230 --> 00:07:31.190 align:middle line:90%
wander far away.

00:07:31.190 --> 00:07:33.880 align:middle line:90%


00:07:33.880 --> 00:07:37.725 align:middle line:84%
The long legs are the horses who
often stray far from the camp.

00:07:37.725 --> 00:07:42.535 align:middle line:90%


00:07:42.535 --> 00:07:46.000 align:middle line:90%
[ORIENTAL MUSIC PLAYING]

00:07:46.000 --> 00:07:50.950 align:middle line:90%
[SPEAKING MONGOLIAN]

00:07:50.950 --> 00:07:55.900 align:middle line:90%


00:07:55.900 --> 00:07:59.860 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH SINGING]

00:07:59.860 --> 00:08:04.900 align:middle line:84%
>> Life goes on governed by
the vagaries of the wind,

00:08:04.900 --> 00:08:08.480 align:middle line:84%
the presence of wolves, and
the height of the grass under

00:08:08.480 --> 00:08:09.470 align:middle line:90%
a vivid blue sky.

00:08:09.470 --> 00:08:16.685 align:middle line:90%


00:08:16.685 --> 00:08:19.050 align:middle line:84%
The Mongols have always
looked on the sky

00:08:19.050 --> 00:08:19.980 align:middle line:90%
as their common room.

00:08:19.980 --> 00:08:22.793 align:middle line:90%


00:08:22.793 --> 00:08:23.960 align:middle line:90%
They have made it their god.

00:08:23.960 --> 00:08:27.880 align:middle line:90%


00:08:27.880 --> 00:08:30.635 align:middle line:84%
They call it the Tengri,
and it's the oldest wood

00:08:30.635 --> 00:08:31.435 align:middle line:90%
in their language.

00:08:31.435 --> 00:08:36.660 align:middle line:90%


00:08:36.660 --> 00:08:40.880 align:middle line:10%
>> For a long time, the Mongols
had only the sky for a god.

00:08:40.880 --> 00:08:41.876 align:middle line:90%
[HORSE SNORTING]

00:08:41.876 --> 00:08:45.860 align:middle line:90%
[SPEAKING MONGOLIAN]

00:08:45.860 --> 00:08:51.680 align:middle line:84%
And then in the 16th century,
Buddhism came to these plains.

00:08:51.680 --> 00:08:54.680 align:middle line:84%
The first temples were
built, and notably the temple

00:08:54.680 --> 00:08:57.890 align:middle line:90%
of Erdene Zuu.

00:08:57.890 --> 00:09:01.310 align:middle line:84%
It's situated very near a
Karakorum, the ancient Mongol

00:09:01.310 --> 00:09:03.500 align:middle line:90%
capital created by Genghis Khan.

00:09:03.500 --> 00:09:09.320 align:middle line:90%


00:09:09.320 --> 00:09:12.200 align:middle line:84%
Completely ringed by
a brick wall, topped

00:09:12.200 --> 00:09:16.460 align:middle line:84%
by more than 100 stupors,
this is the most ancient

00:09:16.460 --> 00:09:18.080 align:middle line:84%
and the biggest
temple in the country.

00:09:18.080 --> 00:09:31.121 align:middle line:90%


00:09:31.121 --> 00:09:33.755 align:middle line:84%
>> Buddhism finally spread
to the whole of Mongolia.

00:09:33.755 --> 00:09:36.260 align:middle line:90%


00:09:36.260 --> 00:09:38.030 align:middle line:10%
At the beginning of
the 20th century,

00:09:38.030 --> 00:09:42.070 align:middle line:10%
the country had more
than 700 monasteries.

00:09:42.070 --> 00:09:44.820 align:middle line:84%
But most of them were destroyed
during the Cultural Revolution

00:09:44.820 --> 00:09:51.580 align:middle line:84%
of 1937, when 20,000
lamas were put to death.

00:09:51.580 --> 00:09:57.790 align:middle line:90%


00:09:57.790 --> 00:10:02.800 align:middle line:84%
The Mongols have regained their
freedom of worship since 1990.

00:10:02.800 --> 00:10:05.500 align:middle line:84%
Their religion, which is
inspired by Tibetan Buddhism,

00:10:05.500 --> 00:10:07.030 align:middle line:90%
is very strong.

00:10:07.030 --> 00:10:09.426 align:middle line:84%
But it has not
displaced shamanism.

00:10:09.426 --> 00:10:15.614 align:middle line:90%


00:10:15.614 --> 00:10:18.970 align:middle line:84%
>> This statue is one of the
last vestiges of the ancient

00:10:18.970 --> 00:10:21.910 align:middle line:90%
Mongol capital.

00:10:21.910 --> 00:10:26.720 align:middle line:84%
There were four like this
at each corner of the town.

00:10:26.720 --> 00:10:29.740 align:middle line:84%
The tortoise, linked with
the spirit of the waters,

00:10:29.740 --> 00:10:32.330 align:middle line:84%
was supposed to protect
Karakorum from floods.

00:10:32.330 --> 00:10:35.410 align:middle line:90%
[SPEAKING MONGOLIAN]

00:10:35.410 --> 00:10:38.470 align:middle line:84%
Today, people still
come to pray to him.

00:10:38.470 --> 00:10:40.690 align:middle line:84%
They lay stones and
they make offerings.

00:10:40.690 --> 00:10:49.054 align:middle line:90%


00:10:49.054 --> 00:10:54.450 align:middle line:84%
>> In fact, the Mongols have
never given up shamanism.

00:10:54.450 --> 00:10:57.230 align:middle line:84%
They've integrated it into
their own form of Buddhism.

00:10:57.230 --> 00:11:00.158 align:middle line:90%


00:11:00.158 --> 00:11:03.086 align:middle line:84%
They still believe in the
spirits of the landscape.

00:11:03.086 --> 00:11:08.942 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:11:08.942 --> 00:11:17.726 align:middle line:90%


00:11:17.726 --> 00:11:22.960 align:middle line:84%
>> In one year, a Mongol
moves on six or seven times,

00:11:22.960 --> 00:11:28.280 align:middle line:84%
depending on the
season, the vegetation,

00:11:28.280 --> 00:11:29.570 align:middle line:90%
and the needs of his animals.

00:11:29.570 --> 00:11:34.020 align:middle line:90%


00:11:34.020 --> 00:11:37.170 align:middle line:84%
But each time, when
he puts up his yurt,

00:11:37.170 --> 00:11:39.900 align:middle line:84%
he pays strict attention
to its correct orientation.

00:11:39.900 --> 00:11:42.828 align:middle line:90%


00:11:42.828 --> 00:11:45.380 align:middle line:84%
>> The door is
always facing south.

00:11:45.380 --> 00:11:52.090 align:middle line:90%


00:11:52.090 --> 00:11:54.985 align:middle line:84%
Inside the tent, too, everything
is always in the same place.

00:11:54.985 --> 00:11:58.840 align:middle line:90%


00:11:58.840 --> 00:12:07.870 align:middle line:84%
The men sit on the west
side, the women on the east.

00:12:07.870 --> 00:12:09.860 align:middle line:84%
The north-facing side
of the yurt is sacred.

00:12:09.860 --> 00:12:12.650 align:middle line:90%


00:12:12.650 --> 00:12:15.668 align:middle line:84%
The family's most valuable
possessions are kept there.

00:12:15.668 --> 00:12:19.970 align:middle line:90%
[ORIENTAL MUSIC PLAYING]

00:12:19.970 --> 00:12:22.360 align:middle line:90%


00:12:22.360 --> 00:12:25.110 align:middle line:84%
Only the most respected people
are allowed to go in there.

00:12:25.110 --> 00:12:30.533 align:middle line:90%


00:12:30.533 --> 00:12:33.890 align:middle line:84%
>> It's also in the northern
part that the Mongols raised

00:12:33.890 --> 00:12:37.390 align:middle line:84%
the small altar, which
is found in every yurt.

00:12:37.390 --> 00:12:41.170 align:middle line:84%
With its butter lamps and
its photo of the Dalai Lama.

00:12:41.170 --> 00:12:50.594 align:middle line:90%


00:12:50.594 --> 00:12:54.180 align:middle line:84%
>> This small ceremony bears
witness again to the importance

00:12:54.180 --> 00:12:58.420 align:middle line:84%
Mongols give to the
cardinal points.

00:12:58.420 --> 00:13:01.240 align:middle line:84%
When horsemen leave the
camp, the four directions

00:13:01.240 --> 00:13:03.700 align:middle line:84%
are blessed each in
turn with mare's milk.

00:13:03.700 --> 00:13:09.150 align:middle line:90%


00:13:09.150 --> 00:13:12.510 align:middle line:84%
This is a sure way not to
forget the superior powers.

00:13:12.510 --> 00:13:16.956 align:middle line:90%
[ORIENTAL MUSIC PLAYING]

00:13:16.956 --> 00:13:23.872 align:middle line:90%


00:13:23.872 --> 00:13:28.820 align:middle line:84%
>> Man has always needed to
localize the invisible world,

00:13:28.820 --> 00:13:34.870 align:middle line:84%
to situate in relation to his
own universe, his own horizons.

00:13:34.870 --> 00:13:37.990 align:middle line:84%
He has often taken the cardinal
points into consideration

00:13:37.990 --> 00:13:41.095 align:middle line:84%
when building his holy places
or practicing his rituals.

00:13:41.095 --> 00:14:01.250 align:middle line:90%


00:14:01.250 --> 00:14:04.590 align:middle line:84%
>> On the Mayan site of
Chichen Itza in Mexico,

00:14:04.590 --> 00:14:08.640 align:middle line:84%
the main pyramid, El Castillo,
was very precisely orientated

00:14:08.640 --> 00:14:11.160 align:middle line:84%
when it was built in the
middle of the Grand Esplanade.

00:14:11.160 --> 00:14:18.130 align:middle line:90%


00:14:18.130 --> 00:14:21.420 align:middle line:84%
The Mayas saw the Earth
as a flat, square shape,

00:14:21.420 --> 00:14:23.340 align:middle line:84%
with each corner at
a cardinal point.

00:14:23.340 --> 00:14:28.950 align:middle line:90%


00:14:28.950 --> 00:14:31.770 align:middle line:84%
To be in harmony with the
Earth, the four staircases

00:14:31.770 --> 00:14:34.485 align:middle line:84%
of the pyramid are facing
the four cardinal points.

00:14:34.485 --> 00:14:44.640 align:middle line:90%


00:14:44.640 --> 00:14:48.960 align:middle line:84%
>> A few dozen meters from
El Castillo, to the west,

00:14:48.960 --> 00:14:50.685 align:middle line:84%
there's a construction
open to the sky.

00:14:50.685 --> 00:14:54.927 align:middle line:90%


00:14:54.927 --> 00:14:57.135 align:middle line:84%
This is an area where they
played the game of pelota.

00:14:57.135 --> 00:15:02.330 align:middle line:90%


00:15:02.330 --> 00:15:05.890 align:middle line:10%
Two high walls face
each other, each one

00:15:05.890 --> 00:15:08.202 align:middle line:10%
has a stone ring set in it.

00:15:08.202 --> 00:15:12.870 align:middle line:90%


00:15:12.870 --> 00:15:16.350 align:middle line:84%
The game of pelota
was a team game.

00:15:16.350 --> 00:15:18.360 align:middle line:84%
The players had to get
a heavy rubber ball

00:15:18.360 --> 00:15:20.280 align:middle line:90%
from one side to the other.

00:15:20.280 --> 00:15:24.540 align:middle line:10%
And if possible, get it to go
through one of the rings fixed

00:15:24.540 --> 00:15:25.845 align:middle line:10%
eight meters above the ground.

00:15:25.845 --> 00:15:32.600 align:middle line:90%


00:15:32.600 --> 00:15:38.110 align:middle line:84%
>> The game was difficult.
The stakes, terrifying.

00:15:38.110 --> 00:15:43.100 align:middle line:90%


00:15:43.100 --> 00:15:47.120 align:middle line:84%
The loser was quite
simply beheaded.

00:15:47.120 --> 00:15:51.800 align:middle line:84%
As we can see in this scene,
which is carved into the wall,

00:15:51.800 --> 00:15:53.270 align:middle line:84%
the captain of the
winning team is

00:15:53.270 --> 00:15:57.760 align:middle line:84%
holding a flint knife in one
hand, and in the other hand

00:15:57.760 --> 00:15:58.740 align:middle line:90%
the head of the loser.

00:15:58.740 --> 00:16:03.270 align:middle line:90%


00:16:03.270 --> 00:16:06.760 align:middle line:10%
The head was probably
then displayed nearby

00:16:06.760 --> 00:16:10.360 align:middle line:10%
on this platform whose design
suggests its sinister use.

00:16:10.360 --> 00:16:27.685 align:middle line:90%


00:16:27.685 --> 00:16:31.520 align:middle line:84%
>> Experts in Mayan culture
think that this ball game was

00:16:31.520 --> 00:16:34.880 align:middle line:84%
not so much a sport but more
of a ritual with a cosmic

00:16:34.880 --> 00:16:35.906 align:middle line:90%
dimension.

00:16:35.906 --> 00:16:40.010 align:middle line:90%


00:16:40.010 --> 00:16:43.130 align:middle line:84%
The ball went
backwards and forwards.

00:16:43.130 --> 00:16:45.230 align:middle line:84%
This was probably an
evocation of the movements

00:16:45.230 --> 00:16:46.490 align:middle line:90%
of the planets and the sun.

00:16:46.490 --> 00:16:51.792 align:middle line:90%


00:16:51.792 --> 00:16:57.040 align:middle line:84%
>> The Mayans were fascinated
by the heavenly bodies.

00:16:57.040 --> 00:16:59.770 align:middle line:84%
At Chichen Itza, this
small circular building

00:16:59.770 --> 00:17:01.465 align:middle line:84%
was probably for
observing the stars.

00:17:01.465 --> 00:17:06.619 align:middle line:90%


00:17:06.619 --> 00:17:08.349 align:middle line:84%
The narrow openings
in the walls are

00:17:08.349 --> 00:17:10.750 align:middle line:84%
aligned so that they
correspond to the positions

00:17:10.750 --> 00:17:13.462 align:middle line:84%
of the moon and certain
planets on key days

00:17:13.462 --> 00:17:14.379 align:middle line:90%
of the Mayan calendar.

00:17:14.379 --> 00:17:22.810 align:middle line:90%


00:17:22.810 --> 00:17:26.260 align:middle line:84%
>> Man has often considered
the position and the movement

00:17:26.260 --> 00:17:30.020 align:middle line:84%
of the stars and the universe
as the supreme expression

00:17:30.020 --> 00:17:30.900 align:middle line:90%
of divine order.

00:17:30.900 --> 00:17:35.450 align:middle line:90%


00:17:35.450 --> 00:17:37.450 align:middle line:84%
And he has tried to
decipher the principles

00:17:37.450 --> 00:17:39.985 align:middle line:84%
and workings of an
infinitely complex creation.

00:17:39.985 --> 00:17:50.210 align:middle line:90%


00:17:50.210 --> 00:17:54.260 align:middle line:84%
>> There is in fact only one
astral cycle that everyone can

00:17:54.260 --> 00:17:57.830 align:middle line:84%
understand and relate
to, that of the sun.

00:17:57.830 --> 00:18:03.260 align:middle line:90%


00:18:03.260 --> 00:18:06.530 align:middle line:90%
It rises, it sets.

00:18:06.530 --> 00:18:10.220 align:middle line:84%
It is the absolute master of
the rhythms of life on Earth.

00:18:10.220 --> 00:18:11.880 align:middle line:84%
This is the proof
of its great power.

00:18:11.880 --> 00:18:17.180 align:middle line:90%


00:18:17.180 --> 00:18:19.500 align:middle line:84%
In many civilizations,
it is considered

00:18:19.500 --> 00:18:20.990 align:middle line:90%
as the primordial deity.

00:18:20.990 --> 00:18:27.230 align:middle line:90%


00:18:27.230 --> 00:18:32.060 align:middle line:84%
>> Indians, Hindus, Incas,
and Aztecs have all worshipped

00:18:32.060 --> 00:18:34.430 align:middle line:90%
the sun.

00:18:34.430 --> 00:18:37.190 align:middle line:84%
But it is without
doubt in Egypt that it

00:18:37.190 --> 00:18:38.415 align:middle line:90%
has been venerated longest.

00:18:38.415 --> 00:18:42.260 align:middle line:90%


00:18:42.260 --> 00:18:45.180 align:middle line:84%
The tombs, the stelas,
and the monuments

00:18:45.180 --> 00:18:48.480 align:middle line:84%
that have lasted until
today are full of references

00:18:48.480 --> 00:18:54.856 align:middle line:90%
to the solar occult.

00:18:54.856 --> 00:18:58.700 align:middle line:84%
>> The pyramids pointing towards
the sky symbolize the ladder

00:18:58.700 --> 00:19:02.260 align:middle line:90%
by which man can reach the sun.

00:19:02.260 --> 00:19:03.850 align:middle line:84%
They house the tomb
of the pharaoh,

00:19:03.850 --> 00:19:06.550 align:middle line:84%
who was considered as the
earthly incarnation of the sun.

00:19:06.550 --> 00:19:13.640 align:middle line:90%


00:19:13.640 --> 00:19:16.540 align:middle line:84%
It is represented here
in the guise of Amon Ra.

00:19:16.540 --> 00:19:23.875 align:middle line:90%


00:19:23.875 --> 00:19:26.320 align:middle line:84%
>> Throughout the
many dynasties,

00:19:26.320 --> 00:19:30.460 align:middle line:84%
the Egyptians have represented
the sun god under many forms.

00:19:30.460 --> 00:19:33.820 align:middle line:84%
On this stela, the
divinity has a human body,

00:19:33.820 --> 00:19:36.430 align:middle line:84%
the head of a falcon,
and a headdress

00:19:36.430 --> 00:19:39.070 align:middle line:90%
in the form of a solar disk.

00:19:39.070 --> 00:19:40.240 align:middle line:90%
This is Ra-Horakhty.

00:19:40.240 --> 00:19:46.694 align:middle line:90%


00:19:46.694 --> 00:19:49.890 align:middle line:10%
>> When the sun set, the
Egyptians said it was

00:19:49.890 --> 00:19:53.600 align:middle line:10%
descending into the underworld.

00:19:53.600 --> 00:19:56.660 align:middle line:10%
That it was leaving on its
boat to confront Apophis,

00:19:56.660 --> 00:19:59.748 align:middle line:10%
the great snake who wanted
to prevent the return of day.

00:19:59.748 --> 00:20:12.450 align:middle line:90%


00:20:12.450 --> 00:20:15.000 align:middle line:84%
Mythologies and religions
are almost universally

00:20:15.000 --> 00:20:16.950 align:middle line:84%
in accordance
concerning the partition

00:20:16.950 --> 00:20:18.270 align:middle line:90%
of the tangible universe.

00:20:18.270 --> 00:20:21.070 align:middle line:90%


00:20:21.070 --> 00:20:23.680 align:middle line:90%
There are two worlds--

00:20:23.680 --> 00:20:26.950 align:middle line:84%
the celestial world
associated with light,

00:20:26.950 --> 00:20:30.340 align:middle line:84%
and the underworld
associated with darkness.

00:20:30.340 --> 00:20:32.575 align:middle line:84%
And each world has its
own gods and demons.

00:20:32.575 --> 00:20:39.832 align:middle line:90%


00:20:39.832 --> 00:20:44.330 align:middle line:84%
>> Caves and openings in the
rock very probably figured

00:20:44.330 --> 00:20:47.510 align:middle line:84%
in the origins of entry points
into the world of shadows.

00:20:47.510 --> 00:20:52.910 align:middle line:90%


00:20:52.910 --> 00:20:55.730 align:middle line:84%
But at the same time,
they served as shelters

00:20:55.730 --> 00:20:57.365 align:middle line:84%
against the cold
and wild animals.

00:20:57.365 --> 00:21:01.100 align:middle line:90%


00:21:01.100 --> 00:21:04.610 align:middle line:84%
Thence came the confusing idea
that within these cavities

00:21:04.610 --> 00:21:07.700 align:middle line:84%
the Earth was offering land
the warmth and protection

00:21:07.700 --> 00:21:08.780 align:middle line:90%
of the maternal womb.

00:21:08.780 --> 00:21:12.848 align:middle line:90%


00:21:12.848 --> 00:21:15.500 align:middle line:84%
>> So the Earth was
the mother of humanity.

00:21:15.500 --> 00:21:18.010 align:middle line:90%


00:21:18.010 --> 00:21:22.310 align:middle line:84%
And this idea gave rise to cults
devoted to mother goddesses,

00:21:22.310 --> 00:21:25.590 align:middle line:84%
incarnating both the Earth and
fertility at the same time.

00:21:25.590 --> 00:21:29.500 align:middle line:90%


00:21:29.500 --> 00:21:32.710 align:middle line:84%
This ivory statue was discovered
in France in the Haute-Garonne

00:21:32.710 --> 00:21:34.480 align:middle line:90%
Department.

00:21:34.480 --> 00:21:37.480 align:middle line:90%
It's about 23,000 years old.

00:21:37.480 --> 00:21:39.950 align:middle line:90%
It's the Venus of Lespugue.

00:21:39.950 --> 00:21:41.500 align:middle line:84%
It's thought to be
a representation

00:21:41.500 --> 00:21:42.992 align:middle line:90%
of a primitive idol.

00:21:42.992 --> 00:21:46.768 align:middle line:90%
[CHANTING]

00:21:46.768 --> 00:21:49.600 align:middle line:90%


00:21:49.600 --> 00:21:52.780 align:middle line:84%
>> This small
stature has no feet,

00:21:52.780 --> 00:21:55.780 align:middle line:84%
and its legs are tapered
towards the bottom.

00:21:55.780 --> 00:21:58.120 align:middle line:84%
This was perhaps so
that the statue could

00:21:58.120 --> 00:22:00.490 align:middle line:84%
be planted into the
earth, thus creating

00:22:00.490 --> 00:22:03.620 align:middle line:84%
a magic link between the
fecundity it represented

00:22:03.620 --> 00:22:05.405 align:middle line:90%
and the fertility of the ground.

00:22:05.405 --> 00:22:11.580 align:middle line:90%
[WATER RUNNING]

00:22:11.580 --> 00:22:16.640 align:middle line:84%
>> Caves, fissures-- these
have fired the imaginations

00:22:16.640 --> 00:22:19.280 align:middle line:84%
of communities who have often
associated them with female

00:22:19.280 --> 00:22:21.190 align:middle line:90%
organs.

00:22:21.190 --> 00:22:24.470 align:middle line:84%
And they bring forth from the
bowels of the Earth heroes

00:22:24.470 --> 00:22:26.136 align:middle line:90%
and gods.

00:22:26.136 --> 00:22:32.052 align:middle line:90%
[WATER RUNNING]

00:22:32.052 --> 00:22:39.960 align:middle line:90%


00:22:39.960 --> 00:22:42.000 align:middle line:84%
If we believe the
legend that the god Zeus

00:22:42.000 --> 00:22:44.640 align:middle line:84%
himself was born
in this cave, which

00:22:44.640 --> 00:22:47.310 align:middle line:84%
opens onto the slopes of
Mount Dikteon in Crete.

00:22:47.310 --> 00:22:57.110 align:middle line:90%


00:22:57.110 --> 00:23:01.130 align:middle line:84%
Zeus then went to Mount Olympus,
the highest mountain in Greece,

00:23:01.130 --> 00:23:03.870 align:middle line:84%
where, according to legend,
the gods of the Greek pantheon

00:23:03.870 --> 00:23:04.670 align:middle line:90%
lived.

00:23:04.670 --> 00:23:14.792 align:middle line:90%


00:23:14.792 --> 00:23:18.730 align:middle line:84%
>> Less than 100 kilometers
away from Zeus' residence,

00:23:18.730 --> 00:23:21.770 align:middle line:84%
this incredible chaos of
rocks has taken on a sacred

00:23:21.770 --> 00:23:22.570 align:middle line:90%
dimension.

00:23:22.570 --> 00:23:25.540 align:middle line:90%


00:23:25.540 --> 00:23:29.770 align:middle line:84%
This mass of rocky spires is
situated in central Greece

00:23:29.770 --> 00:23:31.892 align:middle line:90%
on the Plain of Thessaly.

00:23:31.892 --> 00:23:33.100 align:middle line:90%
This is the site of Meteora--

00:23:33.100 --> 00:23:35.740 align:middle line:90%


00:23:35.740 --> 00:23:39.297 align:middle line:84%
Meteora meaning literally
hanging in the air.

00:23:39.297 --> 00:23:43.770 align:middle line:90%
[SPIRITUAL MUSIC PLAYING]

00:23:43.770 --> 00:23:54.704 align:middle line:90%


00:23:54.704 --> 00:23:58.220 align:middle line:84%
>> We find that men settled
at the top of these cliffs,

00:23:58.220 --> 00:24:00.350 align:middle line:84%
some of which are
400 meters high.

00:24:00.350 --> 00:24:03.680 align:middle line:90%


00:24:03.680 --> 00:24:05.120 align:middle line:90%
There they built monasteries.

00:24:05.120 --> 00:24:08.150 align:middle line:90%


00:24:08.150 --> 00:24:11.030 align:middle line:84%
These buildings date from
the 14th and 15th centuries.

00:24:11.030 --> 00:24:21.170 align:middle line:90%


00:24:21.170 --> 00:24:24.170 align:middle line:84%
Byzantine monks had settled
there 300 years earlier.

00:24:24.170 --> 00:24:27.260 align:middle line:90%


00:24:27.260 --> 00:24:30.060 align:middle line:84%
They then lived in caves, which
can be seen all over this rock

00:24:30.060 --> 00:24:30.860 align:middle line:90%
face.

00:24:30.860 --> 00:24:35.520 align:middle line:90%


00:24:35.520 --> 00:24:39.703 align:middle line:84%
And one day, they decided to
leave these unsafe shelters.

00:24:39.703 --> 00:24:41.120 align:middle line:84%
And after many
great efforts, they

00:24:41.120 --> 00:24:44.209 align:middle line:84%
settled at the top of
these steepling outcrops.

00:24:44.209 --> 00:24:47.562 align:middle line:90%
[RELIGIOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

00:24:47.562 --> 00:24:54.747 align:middle line:90%
[BELL RINGING]

00:24:54.747 --> 00:24:57.760 align:middle line:84%
>> We might think that it was
their desire to get closer

00:24:57.760 --> 00:25:00.310 align:middle line:84%
to God which led
them to do this.

00:25:00.310 --> 00:25:03.430 align:middle line:90%
The truth is more prosaic.

00:25:03.430 --> 00:25:06.780 align:middle line:84%
It was to escape persecution
by the Turks and Albanians.

00:25:06.780 --> 00:25:11.208 align:middle line:90%
[RELIGIOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

00:25:11.208 --> 00:25:20.560 align:middle line:90%


00:25:20.560 --> 00:25:23.530 align:middle line:84%
In those times, they can
only reach these refuges

00:25:23.530 --> 00:25:26.890 align:middle line:84%
by using long, movable
ladders, or being hoisted up

00:25:26.890 --> 00:25:27.860 align:middle line:90%
by a rope and winch.

00:25:27.860 --> 00:25:36.433 align:middle line:90%


00:25:36.433 --> 00:25:41.990 align:middle line:84%
>> The monks built more
than 20 monasteries.

00:25:41.990 --> 00:25:44.660 align:middle line:84%
Many were destroyed during
the Second World War

00:25:44.660 --> 00:25:49.130 align:middle line:84%
because they were used
by the Greek resistance.

00:25:49.130 --> 00:25:50.585 align:middle line:90%
Five of them are still occupied.

00:25:50.585 --> 00:25:54.140 align:middle line:90%


00:25:54.140 --> 00:25:56.690 align:middle line:84%
The ancients called them
monasteries of the air.

00:25:56.690 --> 00:26:00.270 align:middle line:90%


00:26:00.270 --> 00:26:02.820 align:middle line:84%
They said that the rocks had
been specially sent by heaven

00:26:02.820 --> 00:26:05.850 align:middle line:84%
to provide the monks with a
refuge from whence prayers

00:26:05.850 --> 00:26:07.590 align:middle line:90%
would easily rise up to God.

00:26:07.590 --> 00:26:12.310 align:middle line:90%


00:26:12.310 --> 00:26:16.270 align:middle line:84%
>> The idea that the higher
one can get the closer one is

00:26:16.270 --> 00:26:20.560 align:middle line:84%
to God, is ancient
and universal.

00:26:20.560 --> 00:26:23.350 align:middle line:84%
In the Bible, it's the
story of the Tower of Babel.

00:26:23.350 --> 00:26:27.980 align:middle line:90%
[MIDDLE EASTERN MUSIC PLAYING]

00:26:27.980 --> 00:26:30.140 align:middle line:84%
This tale no doubt
takes its inspiration

00:26:30.140 --> 00:26:33.320 align:middle line:84%
from the huge high rise
constructions in Mesopotamia,

00:26:33.320 --> 00:26:34.780 align:middle line:90%
which were called ziggurats.

00:26:34.780 --> 00:26:37.522 align:middle line:90%


00:26:37.522 --> 00:26:41.410 align:middle line:10%
>> In fact, it denounces
human ambition.

00:26:41.410 --> 00:26:44.850 align:middle line:84%
Man, having acquired the
technique of construction,

00:26:44.850 --> 00:26:47.070 align:middle line:84%
was thought to have become
very sure of himself

00:26:47.070 --> 00:26:50.550 align:middle line:84%
and wanted to reach heaven,
which is good as man

00:26:50.550 --> 00:26:51.980 align:middle line:90%
taking the place of God.

00:26:51.980 --> 00:27:00.010 align:middle line:90%


00:27:00.010 --> 00:27:01.960 align:middle line:84%
By their very
nature, deities must

00:27:01.960 --> 00:27:07.310 align:middle line:84%
live in the place which is
difficult for man to reach,

00:27:07.310 --> 00:27:10.370 align:middle line:84%
like for example
the mountain, which

00:27:10.370 --> 00:27:12.350 align:middle line:84%
is considered by
various civilizations

00:27:12.350 --> 00:27:15.566 align:middle line:90%
as the domain of the gods.

00:27:15.566 --> 00:27:18.530 align:middle line:84%
>> Sacred mountains
are found everywhere,

00:27:18.530 --> 00:27:21.690 align:middle line:84%
even if they're not
worshipped for themselves,

00:27:21.690 --> 00:27:25.950 align:middle line:84%
even if they are not the
home of gods or spirits.

00:27:25.950 --> 00:27:31.520 align:middle line:84%
Such height so connected with
an idea of spiritual elevation.

00:27:31.520 --> 00:27:34.740 align:middle line:84%
>> They take man away from the
earthbound nature of his daily

00:27:34.740 --> 00:27:35.930 align:middle line:90%
life.

00:27:35.930 --> 00:27:37.910 align:middle line:84%
They are the symbol
of higher ambition.

00:27:37.910 --> 00:27:42.510 align:middle line:90%


00:27:42.510 --> 00:27:46.690 align:middle line:84%
Mountains are often volcanoes,
so their spiritual import

00:27:46.690 --> 00:27:47.550 align:middle line:90%
is even stronger.

00:27:47.550 --> 00:27:56.440 align:middle line:90%


00:27:56.440 --> 00:27:59.410 align:middle line:84%
The legend author Virgil claims
that the forge of Vulcan,

00:27:59.410 --> 00:28:03.310 align:middle line:84%
the god of fire, was
located here in Sicily.

00:28:03.310 --> 00:28:06.190 align:middle line:84%
Etna, he said, was
Vulcan's workshop,

00:28:06.190 --> 00:28:07.960 align:middle line:84%
which is why we
see these plumes,

00:28:07.960 --> 00:28:10.403 align:middle line:90%
this activity on the surface.

00:28:10.403 --> 00:28:13.644 align:middle line:90%
[VOLCANO ERUPTING]

00:28:13.644 --> 00:28:18.430 align:middle line:84%
>> Tradition has it that
Vulcan was the son of Jupiter.

00:28:18.430 --> 00:28:21.850 align:middle line:84%
The cyclops helped
him in his work.

00:28:21.850 --> 00:28:24.220 align:middle line:84%
He mastered molten
magic, and with it

00:28:24.220 --> 00:28:27.210 align:middle line:90%
made jewels and weapons.

00:28:27.210 --> 00:28:29.835 align:middle line:10%
It is said that he forged the
shield of the hero Achilles.

00:28:29.835 --> 00:28:45.100 align:middle line:90%


00:28:45.100 --> 00:28:48.740 align:middle line:84%
When lava starts to well up
from the bowels of the Earth,

00:28:48.740 --> 00:28:51.990 align:middle line:84%
Virgil is persuaded that this is
the blood of giants vanquished

00:28:51.990 --> 00:28:52.790 align:middle line:90%
by the gods.

00:28:52.790 --> 00:29:02.305 align:middle line:90%


00:29:02.305 --> 00:29:06.170 align:middle line:84%
>> The ancient Greeks
had another version.

00:29:06.170 --> 00:29:09.920 align:middle line:84%
They say that if the Earth
spews out lava and smoke here,

00:29:09.920 --> 00:29:13.010 align:middle line:84%
it's because Typhon,
the 100-headed monster,

00:29:13.010 --> 00:29:15.740 align:middle line:84%
is raging against the
gods who chained him up

00:29:15.740 --> 00:29:16.860 align:middle line:90%
in the depths of Etna.

00:29:16.860 --> 00:29:24.430 align:middle line:90%


00:29:24.430 --> 00:29:26.720 align:middle line:84%
The houses of gods
or of monsters,

00:29:26.720 --> 00:29:30.080 align:middle line:84%
volcanoes inspire in the
imagination of all the power

00:29:30.080 --> 00:29:31.040 align:middle line:90%
of earthly energy.

00:29:31.040 --> 00:29:33.992 align:middle line:90%


00:29:33.992 --> 00:29:37.390 align:middle line:84%
>> An eruption is often
perceived as anger,

00:29:37.390 --> 00:29:40.690 align:middle line:84%
the tangible proof of the
vexation of superior powers.

00:29:40.690 --> 00:29:46.314 align:middle line:90%


00:29:46.314 --> 00:29:49.850 align:middle line:84%
It is written in the
Bible the eternal

00:29:49.850 --> 00:29:53.310 align:middle line:84%
rained fire and brimstone
down on Sodom and Gomorrah.

00:29:53.310 --> 00:30:04.718 align:middle line:90%


00:30:04.718 --> 00:30:07.950 align:middle line:84%
>> Once the Earth is healed,
there remain fractured

00:30:07.950 --> 00:30:10.240 align:middle line:90%
landscapes.

00:30:10.240 --> 00:30:13.990 align:middle line:10%
Solidified lava,
rocks that once again

00:30:13.990 --> 00:30:18.250 align:middle line:10%
stimulate the imagination.

00:30:18.250 --> 00:30:20.590 align:middle line:84%
Here on these shores
in Northern Ireland,

00:30:20.590 --> 00:30:24.598 align:middle line:84%
great volcanic activity
occurred 50 million years ago.

00:30:24.598 --> 00:30:30.682 align:middle line:90%
[SEABIRDS CRYING]

00:30:30.682 --> 00:30:34.900 align:middle line:84%
>> At the foot of these cliffs,
the molten matter as it set

00:30:34.900 --> 00:30:36.970 align:middle line:84%
formed thousands
of basalt columns.

00:30:36.970 --> 00:30:47.455 align:middle line:90%


00:30:47.455 --> 00:30:52.520 align:middle line:84%
>> The polygonal shapes of these
blocks of rock are so perfect

00:30:52.520 --> 00:30:54.770 align:middle line:84%
that for a long time it was
thought that they had been

00:30:54.770 --> 00:30:56.312 align:middle line:90%
shaped from raw matter.

00:30:56.312 --> 00:31:02.590 align:middle line:90%


00:31:02.590 --> 00:31:05.930 align:middle line:84%
There are so many of
them, more than 40,000.

00:31:05.930 --> 00:31:07.450 align:middle line:84%
But they are
believed to have been

00:31:07.450 --> 00:31:11.770 align:middle line:84%
cut by giants who built here the
incredible stone causeway which

00:31:11.770 --> 00:31:15.550 align:middle line:84%
led out into the sea, forming
a bridge with Scotland.

00:31:15.550 --> 00:31:20.330 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:31:20.330 --> 00:31:23.680 align:middle line:90%


00:31:23.680 --> 00:31:25.600 align:middle line:84%
That's the story
that Gaelic legend

00:31:25.600 --> 00:31:28.090 align:middle line:84%
tells about the
Giant's Causeway that

00:31:28.090 --> 00:31:30.080 align:middle line:84%
lies at the foot of
the Antrim plateau.

00:31:30.080 --> 00:31:40.640 align:middle line:90%


00:31:40.640 --> 00:31:44.090 align:middle line:84%
>> When rocks are shaped
like this on a huge scale,

00:31:44.090 --> 00:31:46.730 align:middle line:84%
man tends automatically to
imagine the intervention

00:31:46.730 --> 00:31:48.067 align:middle line:90%
of supernatural beings.

00:31:48.067 --> 00:31:52.270 align:middle line:90%


00:31:52.270 --> 00:31:54.700 align:middle line:84%
His initial theory is
simple because of his lack

00:31:54.700 --> 00:31:57.110 align:middle line:90%
of geological knowledge.

00:31:57.110 --> 00:31:59.360 align:middle line:84%
Who other than
giants or gods would

00:31:59.360 --> 00:32:02.390 align:middle line:84%
be able to fashion rocks
in such vast proportions?

00:32:02.390 --> 00:32:11.730 align:middle line:90%


00:32:11.730 --> 00:32:15.210 align:middle line:84%
The sea itself has
tried its best.

00:32:15.210 --> 00:32:17.370 align:middle line:84%
But throughout the
life of man, this cliff

00:32:17.370 --> 00:32:21.540 align:middle line:84%
has remained more
or less unchanged.

00:32:21.540 --> 00:32:24.015 align:middle line:90%
[WAVES CRASHING]

00:32:24.015 --> 00:32:28.470 align:middle line:90%
[SEABIRDS CRYING]

00:32:28.470 --> 00:32:57.180 align:middle line:90%


00:32:57.180 --> 00:33:01.880 align:middle line:84%
>> This granite outcrop on
Dartmoor in England is simply

00:33:01.880 --> 00:33:05.240 align:middle line:84%
the result of tens of
thousands of years of erosion.

00:33:05.240 --> 00:33:07.400 align:middle line:84%
But man, who is
always noted thus,

00:33:07.400 --> 00:33:11.000 align:middle line:84%
sees in it the requirement of
the gods to honor a stone idol.

00:33:11.000 --> 00:33:19.568 align:middle line:90%


00:33:19.568 --> 00:33:22.010 align:middle line:84%
>> Perhaps because
it was a challenge,

00:33:22.010 --> 00:33:24.080 align:middle line:84%
perhaps because it was
a discipline reserved

00:33:24.080 --> 00:33:26.150 align:middle line:84%
to the powers of
the other world,

00:33:26.150 --> 00:33:28.820 align:middle line:84%
men in their turn started
to work with stone.

00:33:28.820 --> 00:33:33.230 align:middle line:90%


00:33:33.230 --> 00:33:37.520 align:middle line:84%
In fact, they merely moved
them and erected them.

00:33:37.520 --> 00:33:40.250 align:middle line:84%
Raising long stones,
literally men

00:33:40.250 --> 00:33:41.675 align:middle line:90%
here in the Breton language.

00:33:41.675 --> 00:33:47.100 align:middle line:90%


00:33:47.100 --> 00:33:50.080 align:middle line:84%
This practice was common
throughout Western Europe.

00:33:50.080 --> 00:33:52.650 align:middle line:84%
But it is in the region
of Carnac in France

00:33:52.650 --> 00:33:54.870 align:middle line:84%
that we find the biggest
megalithic alignments.

00:33:54.870 --> 00:34:02.160 align:middle line:90%


00:34:02.160 --> 00:34:05.870 align:middle line:84%
>> These menhirs are often
associated with the rituals

00:34:05.870 --> 00:34:07.790 align:middle line:90%
practiced by druids.

00:34:07.790 --> 00:34:09.739 align:middle line:84%
But these stones were
erected and positioned

00:34:09.739 --> 00:34:12.440 align:middle line:84%
by men well before the
Celtic civilization.

00:34:12.440 --> 00:34:17.239 align:middle line:90%


00:34:17.239 --> 00:34:21.409 align:middle line:84%
This was about 6,000 years
ago in the Neolithic period,

00:34:21.409 --> 00:34:24.260 align:middle line:84%
a period when men began
to cultivate the Earth

00:34:24.260 --> 00:34:25.850 align:middle line:90%
and adopt a sedentary life.

00:34:25.850 --> 00:34:30.409 align:middle line:90%


00:34:30.409 --> 00:34:36.661 align:middle line:84%
The druids simply reused
them 2,000 years later.

00:34:36.661 --> 00:34:40.219 align:middle line:84%
>> Many different hypotheses
have been formulated to explain

00:34:40.219 --> 00:34:41.290 align:middle line:90%
why they are there.

00:34:41.290 --> 00:34:45.170 align:middle line:90%


00:34:45.170 --> 00:34:49.000 align:middle line:84%
They could be commemorative
stones or guide

00:34:49.000 --> 00:34:51.447 align:middle line:84%
marks in an early
attempt at astronomy.

00:34:51.447 --> 00:34:55.650 align:middle line:90%


00:34:55.650 --> 00:34:57.520 align:middle line:84%
The interpretation is
all the more difficult

00:34:57.520 --> 00:34:59.380 align:middle line:84%
because these megaliths
are positioned

00:34:59.380 --> 00:35:01.090 align:middle line:90%
in quite an unpredictable way.

00:35:01.090 --> 00:35:06.730 align:middle line:90%


00:35:06.730 --> 00:35:09.310 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes they are connected
to these enormous stone

00:35:09.310 --> 00:35:10.855 align:middle line:90%
tables that are called dolmens.

00:35:10.855 --> 00:35:19.429 align:middle line:90%


00:35:19.429 --> 00:35:22.960 align:middle line:84%
>> These dolmens gave up
their secret early in the 19th

00:35:22.960 --> 00:35:24.670 align:middle line:90%
century.

00:35:24.670 --> 00:35:26.770 align:middle line:84%
After a series of
excavations, it

00:35:26.770 --> 00:35:29.110 align:middle line:84%
was proved that they
were funeral monuments.

00:35:29.110 --> 00:35:32.720 align:middle line:90%


00:35:32.720 --> 00:35:36.340 align:middle line:84%
But the mystery of
menhirs remains intact.

00:35:36.340 --> 00:35:40.240 align:middle line:84%
It's generally agreed that
they had some holy meaning.

00:35:40.240 --> 00:35:42.460 align:middle line:84%
But some sites tend to
bring this into question.

00:35:42.460 --> 00:35:47.930 align:middle line:90%


00:35:47.930 --> 00:35:51.680 align:middle line:84%
>> Here at [NON-ENGLISH SPEAK],,
the north of France,

00:35:51.680 --> 00:35:53.105 align:middle line:90%
the menhirs stand in a circle.

00:35:53.105 --> 00:35:57.900 align:middle line:90%


00:35:57.900 --> 00:36:01.280 align:middle line:90%
Stone circles are quite common.

00:36:01.280 --> 00:36:02.520 align:middle line:90%
They're called cromlechs.

00:36:02.520 --> 00:36:08.240 align:middle line:90%


00:36:08.240 --> 00:36:12.260 align:middle line:84%
The interest of this one is
in the shape of the stones.

00:36:12.260 --> 00:36:13.670 align:middle line:10%
The upper part of
each menhir has

00:36:13.670 --> 00:36:16.790 align:middle line:10%
been shaped in the form
of a heel turned inwards

00:36:16.790 --> 00:36:18.350 align:middle line:10%
towards the center
of the circle.

00:36:18.350 --> 00:36:25.550 align:middle line:90%


00:36:25.550 --> 00:36:28.800 align:middle line:84%
>> Some researchers thought that
there was nothing sacred about

00:36:28.800 --> 00:36:34.040 align:middle line:84%
these stones and that they were
simply uprights for buildings.

00:36:34.040 --> 00:36:36.960 align:middle line:10%
Their notched shape
suggests that they

00:36:36.960 --> 00:36:39.630 align:middle line:10%
were used as an anchoring
point for guide ropes attached

00:36:39.630 --> 00:36:42.990 align:middle line:10%
to a mast, at the top of
which torches were left

00:36:42.990 --> 00:36:45.480 align:middle line:10%
to give a warning to the
surrounding population in case

00:36:45.480 --> 00:36:46.280 align:middle line:10%
of attack.

00:36:46.280 --> 00:36:48.410 align:middle line:90%


00:36:48.410 --> 00:36:51.210 align:middle line:84%
>> This explanation
is now discounted.

00:36:51.210 --> 00:36:54.120 align:middle line:84%
Today, we know that these
stones mark the position

00:36:54.120 --> 00:36:55.125 align:middle line:90%
of a funeral mound.

00:36:55.125 --> 00:36:59.280 align:middle line:90%


00:36:59.280 --> 00:37:02.580 align:middle line:84%
Here, they are called The Maids,
The Puppets, or The Little

00:37:02.580 --> 00:37:07.480 align:middle line:84%
Girls, for they look like human
shapes having a conversation.

00:37:07.480 --> 00:37:10.505 align:middle line:84%
There are still many
stories about them.

00:37:10.505 --> 00:37:13.965 align:middle line:84%
For the thing about stones is
that they encourage mystery.

00:37:13.965 --> 00:37:21.625 align:middle line:90%


00:37:21.625 --> 00:37:25.960 align:middle line:84%
>> Quite near here at L'Ecluse
stands the biggest menhir

00:37:25.960 --> 00:37:28.090 align:middle line:90%
in the region.

00:37:28.090 --> 00:37:29.860 align:middle line:90%
It's called the Devil's Stone.

00:37:29.860 --> 00:37:37.530 align:middle line:90%


00:37:37.530 --> 00:37:39.680 align:middle line:84%
At the top of the
stone can be seen

00:37:39.680 --> 00:37:43.930 align:middle line:84%
marks like the
scratches of a claw.

00:37:43.930 --> 00:37:45.860 align:middle line:84%
They are said to have
been left by a demon.

00:37:45.860 --> 00:37:52.720 align:middle line:90%


00:37:52.720 --> 00:37:55.520 align:middle line:84%
And for anyone who still
doubts that this stone has

00:37:55.520 --> 00:37:59.015 align:middle line:84%
evil powers, let them just look
at how the rock is flaking.

00:37:59.015 --> 00:38:03.500 align:middle line:90%


00:38:03.500 --> 00:38:07.844 align:middle line:84%
They are sure to see the profile
of a very disturbing character.

00:38:07.844 --> 00:38:17.524 align:middle line:90%


00:38:17.524 --> 00:38:21.720 align:middle line:84%
>> These stories often
originated with the church.

00:38:21.720 --> 00:38:25.200 align:middle line:84%
It was one way of discrediting
the stones, which were often

00:38:25.200 --> 00:38:28.930 align:middle line:90%
at the center of pagan cults.

00:38:28.930 --> 00:38:31.060 align:middle line:84%
Powers were often
attributed to them--

00:38:31.060 --> 00:38:34.603 align:middle line:84%
powers of protection, fertility,
fecundity, or healing.

00:38:34.603 --> 00:38:43.790 align:middle line:90%


00:38:43.790 --> 00:38:46.010 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes these were
the same magic powers

00:38:46.010 --> 00:38:49.400 align:middle line:84%
that were attributed to
special trees, a belief which

00:38:49.400 --> 00:38:50.930 align:middle line:90%
still persists here and there.

00:38:50.930 --> 00:38:55.620 align:middle line:90%


00:38:55.620 --> 00:39:00.020 align:middle line:84%
>> In Belgium at Herchies there
is an oak which is worshipped

00:39:00.020 --> 00:39:01.250 align:middle line:90%
in a very special way.

00:39:01.250 --> 00:39:07.010 align:middle line:90%


00:39:07.010 --> 00:39:11.000 align:middle line:84%
People come at night and hang
clothes, personal objects

00:39:11.000 --> 00:39:11.820 align:middle line:90%
on its trunk.

00:39:11.820 --> 00:39:18.736 align:middle line:90%


00:39:18.736 --> 00:39:20.860 align:middle line:84%
>> This comes from
an ancient belief,

00:39:20.860 --> 00:39:24.100 align:middle line:84%
possibly of druidic origin,
whereby in certain conditions

00:39:24.100 --> 00:39:27.510 align:middle line:84%
one can pass on one's pain
to another living being.

00:39:27.510 --> 00:39:35.750 align:middle line:90%


00:39:35.750 --> 00:39:40.170 align:middle line:84%
The best possible medium
is a very ancient tree,

00:39:40.170 --> 00:39:42.660 align:middle line:84%
one which is strong enough
not to be affected itself.

00:39:42.660 --> 00:39:53.920 align:middle line:90%


00:39:53.920 --> 00:39:55.830 align:middle line:10%
The transfer of
pain is carried out

00:39:55.830 --> 00:39:57.990 align:middle line:10%
when a nail which has
touched the sick part

00:39:57.990 --> 00:39:59.281 align:middle line:10%
is gradually hammered in.

00:39:59.281 --> 00:40:10.360 align:middle line:90%


00:40:10.360 --> 00:40:13.420 align:middle line:84%
This nail oak, which
fosters a pagan belief,

00:40:13.420 --> 00:40:15.550 align:middle line:84%
has been renamed
Saint Anthony's Oak.

00:40:15.550 --> 00:40:18.310 align:middle line:90%


00:40:18.310 --> 00:40:21.920 align:middle line:84%
>> Trees with magic powers
are now often adopted

00:40:21.920 --> 00:40:23.417 align:middle line:90%
by the Christian faith.

00:40:23.417 --> 00:40:28.187 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:40:28.187 --> 00:40:32.480 align:middle line:90%


00:40:32.480 --> 00:40:35.180 align:middle line:84%
In the 15th century
at [INAUDIBLE],,

00:40:35.180 --> 00:40:37.760 align:middle line:84%
100 kilometers from
Paris, the plague

00:40:37.760 --> 00:40:40.420 align:middle line:90%
stopped at this clump of elms.

00:40:40.420 --> 00:40:44.190 align:middle line:84%
Ever since, these trees
have been worshipped.

00:40:44.190 --> 00:40:48.110 align:middle line:84%
People hang clothes there,
rags, which serve as messages.

00:40:48.110 --> 00:40:54.074 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:40:54.074 --> 00:41:04.520 align:middle line:90%


00:41:04.520 --> 00:41:06.980 align:middle line:84%
For one's requests
to be heard, people

00:41:06.980 --> 00:41:09.110 align:middle line:84%
come in and the
piece of cloth which

00:41:09.110 --> 00:41:11.295 align:middle line:84%
has touched the head,
the arm, or the chest

00:41:11.295 --> 00:41:12.095 align:middle line:90%
of the sick person.

00:41:12.095 --> 00:41:15.050 align:middle line:90%


00:41:15.050 --> 00:41:17.510 align:middle line:84%
The site here is
devoted to Saint Claude,

00:41:17.510 --> 00:41:19.580 align:middle line:84%
to whom a small chapel
has been dedicated.

00:41:19.580 --> 00:41:24.160 align:middle line:90%


00:41:24.160 --> 00:41:27.170 align:middle line:84%
>> The church has linked itself
all the more easily to these

00:41:27.170 --> 00:41:31.040 align:middle line:84%
practices because the tree
is not really deified.

00:41:31.040 --> 00:41:32.930 align:middle line:84%
It's just a medium
of communication

00:41:32.930 --> 00:41:34.085 align:middle line:90%
with superior powers.

00:41:34.085 --> 00:41:46.040 align:middle line:90%


00:41:46.040 --> 00:41:48.980 align:middle line:84%
Not far from there in
Normandy in the commune

00:41:48.980 --> 00:41:52.730 align:middle line:84%
of Allouville-Bellefosse, there
is a very old pedunculate oak.

00:41:52.730 --> 00:41:56.020 align:middle line:90%


00:41:56.020 --> 00:41:59.630 align:middle line:84%
The tree is more
than 1,000 years old.

00:41:59.630 --> 00:42:01.360 align:middle line:84%
Its missing branches
have been replaced

00:42:01.360 --> 00:42:03.850 align:middle line:84%
by a wooden turret,
a sort of bell tower

00:42:03.850 --> 00:42:08.080 align:middle line:84%
with a cross on the top, as
if it were a church, which

00:42:08.080 --> 00:42:09.010 align:middle line:90%
is almost the case.

00:42:09.010 --> 00:42:15.520 align:middle line:90%


00:42:15.520 --> 00:42:18.640 align:middle line:84%
The trunk, which is completely,
hollow has two levels,

00:42:18.640 --> 00:42:20.830 align:middle line:84%
with a chapel on each
level consecrated

00:42:20.830 --> 00:42:21.925 align:middle line:90%
to Our Lady of Peace.

00:42:21.925 --> 00:42:29.650 align:middle line:90%


00:42:29.650 --> 00:42:33.130 align:middle line:84%
>> This old oak has
become a sanctuary,

00:42:33.130 --> 00:42:36.190 align:middle line:84%
a sort of holy place which
inspires the respect that its

00:42:36.190 --> 00:42:37.255 align:middle line:90%
great age deserves.

00:42:37.255 --> 00:42:49.900 align:middle line:90%


00:42:49.900 --> 00:42:52.750 align:middle line:84%
On every continent,
1,000 year old trees

00:42:52.750 --> 00:42:55.465 align:middle line:84%
have been linked in some way or
another with beliefs or cults.

00:42:55.465 --> 00:43:00.262 align:middle line:90%


00:43:00.262 --> 00:43:03.280 align:middle line:84%
>> This is the case of the
Dragon Tree on the island

00:43:03.280 --> 00:43:06.250 align:middle line:90%
of Tenerife in the Canaries.

00:43:06.250 --> 00:43:08.380 align:middle line:84%
The indigenous
people, the Guanches,

00:43:08.380 --> 00:43:11.140 align:middle line:84%
who were living here before
the arrival of the Spanish,

00:43:11.140 --> 00:43:14.440 align:middle line:84%
worshipped these age-old trees
and performed sacred ceremonies

00:43:14.440 --> 00:43:15.240 align:middle line:90%
around them.

00:43:15.240 --> 00:43:22.680 align:middle line:90%


00:43:22.680 --> 00:43:26.840 align:middle line:84%
>> Supernatural properties and
magic powers have always been

00:43:26.840 --> 00:43:30.270 align:middle line:90%
attributed to this tree.

00:43:30.270 --> 00:43:33.200 align:middle line:84%
This is largely due to the
medicinal and cosmetic virtues

00:43:33.200 --> 00:43:36.920 align:middle line:84%
in the resin, which can be
extracted from its trunk.

00:43:36.920 --> 00:43:39.410 align:middle line:84%
It cures dysentery,
colds, or bleeding.

00:43:39.410 --> 00:43:45.767 align:middle line:90%


00:43:45.767 --> 00:43:49.050 align:middle line:84%
>> Similar therapeutic
properties made the ginkgo

00:43:49.050 --> 00:43:50.990 align:middle line:84%
the object of
veneration in the East.

00:43:50.990 --> 00:43:59.080 align:middle line:90%


00:43:59.080 --> 00:44:00.550 align:middle line:84%
At the end of the
first Millennium,

00:44:00.550 --> 00:44:02.560 align:middle line:84%
this relic tree
which had existed

00:44:02.560 --> 00:44:05.620 align:middle line:84%
since the days of the dinosaurs,
had almost disappeared

00:44:05.620 --> 00:44:07.870 align:middle line:90%
from the face of the Earth.

00:44:07.870 --> 00:44:10.060 align:middle line:84%
Only a few examples
remained in China.

00:44:10.060 --> 00:44:12.200 align:middle line:90%
[ORIENTAL MUSIC PLAYING]

00:44:12.200 --> 00:44:16.740 align:middle line:84%
Buddhist monks harvested the
leaves to make an infusion.

00:44:16.740 --> 00:44:20.075 align:middle line:84%
This beverage was apparently
very beneficial to both body

00:44:20.075 --> 00:44:20.875 align:middle line:90%
and soul.

00:44:20.875 --> 00:44:24.594 align:middle line:90%


00:44:24.594 --> 00:44:28.210 align:middle line:84%
>> Today, we know that these
very special leaves contain

00:44:28.210 --> 00:44:30.970 align:middle line:84%
rare substances which
increase the flow of blood

00:44:30.970 --> 00:44:33.690 align:middle line:84%
in the arteries and are
beneficial for the irrigation

00:44:33.690 --> 00:44:34.490 align:middle line:90%
of the brain.

00:44:34.490 --> 00:44:39.930 align:middle line:90%


00:44:39.930 --> 00:44:43.387 align:middle line:84%
The ginkgo was reintroduced by
the monks in Korea and Japan

00:44:43.387 --> 00:44:44.220 align:middle line:90%
in the 12th century.

00:44:44.220 --> 00:44:46.800 align:middle line:90%


00:44:46.800 --> 00:44:50.670 align:middle line:84%
Since then, it has been
venerated all over Asia.

00:44:50.670 --> 00:44:53.190 align:middle line:84%
In Japan, the ginkgo
is the sacred tree

00:44:53.190 --> 00:44:55.500 align:middle line:90%
found in Shinto temples.

00:44:55.500 --> 00:45:00.810 align:middle line:84%
>> The ginkgo has the unusual
property of being dioecious.

00:45:00.810 --> 00:45:05.910 align:middle line:84%
In other words, the tree has
both male and female specimens.

00:45:05.910 --> 00:45:08.490 align:middle line:84%
They are easily
recognized in autumn

00:45:08.490 --> 00:45:11.460 align:middle line:84%
because the males lose
their leaves earlier

00:45:11.460 --> 00:45:13.750 align:middle line:84%
and the fruit is still
on the female trees.

00:45:13.750 --> 00:45:19.173 align:middle line:90%


00:45:19.173 --> 00:45:23.950 align:middle line:84%
>> The deification of the ginkgo
in the East probably originates

00:45:23.950 --> 00:45:27.460 align:middle line:84%
because the two sexes can be
distinguished and conforms

00:45:27.460 --> 00:45:30.760 align:middle line:84%
to the cult of opposites,
to the dialectic,

00:45:30.760 --> 00:45:32.910 align:middle line:84%
which likes to oppose
the yin to the yang,

00:45:32.910 --> 00:45:36.220 align:middle line:84%
the north to the
south, good to bad.

00:45:36.220 --> 00:45:43.315 align:middle line:90%


00:45:43.315 --> 00:45:46.560 align:middle line:84%
>> Many trees are sacred,
but few are worshipped

00:45:46.560 --> 00:45:48.360 align:middle line:90%
for themselves.

00:45:48.360 --> 00:45:50.820 align:middle line:84%
They are venerated
as living beings,

00:45:50.820 --> 00:45:54.030 align:middle line:84%
silent and wise witnesses
to passing generations.

00:45:54.030 --> 00:45:59.520 align:middle line:90%


00:45:59.520 --> 00:46:01.830 align:middle line:84%
With its leaves touching
the heavens and its roots

00:46:01.830 --> 00:46:04.260 align:middle line:84%
in contact with the
underworld, the tree

00:46:04.260 --> 00:46:07.410 align:middle line:84%
is the very image of the link
between heaven and earth.

00:46:07.410 --> 00:46:12.580 align:middle line:90%


00:46:12.580 --> 00:46:16.890 align:middle line:84%
>> Never mind if the baobab
gives the opposite impression.

00:46:16.890 --> 00:46:19.140 align:middle line:84%
Everyone knows that it
was an angry god who

00:46:19.140 --> 00:46:20.595 align:middle line:90%
planted it upside down.

00:46:20.595 --> 00:46:27.142 align:middle line:90%


00:46:27.142 --> 00:46:31.170 align:middle line:84%
>> This old tree sits in
the middle of the village.

00:46:31.170 --> 00:46:35.670 align:middle line:84%
They used to say that it was
inhabited by maligned spirits.

00:46:35.670 --> 00:46:37.998 align:middle line:84%
Today, that belief
is disappearing.

00:46:37.998 --> 00:46:44.480 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH SINGING]

00:46:44.480 --> 00:46:47.750 align:middle line:84%
The population is turning
away from the cults of nature

00:46:47.750 --> 00:46:50.301 align:middle line:84%
in favor of
monotheistic religions.

00:46:50.301 --> 00:46:53.010 align:middle line:90%


00:46:53.010 --> 00:46:55.440 align:middle line:84%
Indeed, not far
away man does not

00:46:55.440 --> 00:47:00.780 align:middle line:84%
hesitate to open the earth,
to displease it, to rape it,

00:47:00.780 --> 00:47:03.980 align:middle line:84%
to run any risk just to
rip a few grams of gold

00:47:03.980 --> 00:47:04.780 align:middle line:90%
from its belly.

00:47:04.780 --> 00:47:12.130 align:middle line:90%


00:47:12.130 --> 00:47:18.010 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH SINGING]

00:47:18.010 --> 00:47:22.370 align:middle line:84%
>> In this primitive mining
concession in Burkina Faso,

00:47:22.370 --> 00:47:25.880 align:middle line:84%
men with no protection or
equipment descend into holes

00:47:25.880 --> 00:47:28.750 align:middle line:84%
that they've dug with their
hands looking for gold ore.

00:47:28.750 --> 00:47:45.444 align:middle line:90%


00:47:45.444 --> 00:47:51.350 align:middle line:90%
[METAL CLANKING]

00:47:51.350 --> 00:47:54.710 align:middle line:84%
In olden times, it was
thought that minerals formed

00:47:54.710 --> 00:47:57.470 align:middle line:84%
in the heart of the
Earth, rather like a fetus

00:47:57.470 --> 00:47:59.970 align:middle line:90%
develops in the womb.

00:47:59.970 --> 00:48:03.200 align:middle line:84%
And that this womb patiently
transformed the base metal

00:48:03.200 --> 00:48:06.727 align:middle line:84%
into gold, the symbol
of ultimate perfection.

00:48:06.727 --> 00:48:10.206 align:middle line:90%


00:48:10.206 --> 00:48:12.765 align:middle line:84%
>> It was the only metal
worthy of the gods.

00:48:12.765 --> 00:48:16.040 align:middle line:90%


00:48:16.040 --> 00:48:20.290 align:middle line:84%
It was made into chalices,
offering plates, ritual

00:48:20.290 --> 00:48:21.090 align:middle line:90%
statues.

00:48:21.090 --> 00:48:26.930 align:middle line:90%


00:48:26.930 --> 00:48:29.630 align:middle line:84%
Today, the yellow
metal drags in its wake

00:48:29.630 --> 00:48:31.025 align:middle line:90%
a pagan odor of sulfur.

00:48:31.025 --> 00:48:36.450 align:middle line:90%


00:48:36.450 --> 00:48:40.386 align:middle line:84%
The quest is difficult.
The fortune, illusory.

00:48:40.386 --> 00:48:43.860 align:middle line:90%


00:48:43.860 --> 00:48:46.960 align:middle line:84%
A few grains collected
at enormous risk,

00:48:46.960 --> 00:48:49.450 align:middle line:84%
but only finance a
few days existence.

00:48:49.450 --> 00:48:52.145 align:middle line:90%


00:48:52.145 --> 00:48:54.338 align:middle line:90%
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

00:48:54.338 --> 00:49:00.810 align:middle line:90%


00:49:00.810 --> 00:49:04.350 align:middle line:84%
>> 10,000 kilometers away
from this concession,

00:49:04.350 --> 00:49:07.860 align:middle line:84%
gold has retained all its
sacred value in Thailand,

00:49:07.860 --> 00:49:08.860 align:middle line:90%
in the heart of Bangkok.

00:49:08.860 --> 00:49:20.500 align:middle line:90%


00:49:20.500 --> 00:49:23.890 align:middle line:84%
These gold leaves are being
presented as an offering

00:49:23.890 --> 00:49:25.960 align:middle line:84%
by the faithful who
have come to pray

00:49:25.960 --> 00:49:28.420 align:middle line:90%
at the Mausoleum of Erawan.

00:49:28.420 --> 00:49:30.790 align:middle line:84%
This building of
Paris stone, decorated

00:49:30.790 --> 00:49:32.590 align:middle line:84%
with the most
precious materials,

00:49:32.590 --> 00:49:35.494 align:middle line:90%
is dedicated to Brahma.

00:49:35.494 --> 00:49:42.830 align:middle line:84%
>> The Mausoleum was built
in 1956 to placate the gods.

00:49:42.830 --> 00:49:46.400 align:middle line:84%
Nearby, the Thais had started
to build a large hotel,

00:49:46.400 --> 00:49:48.160 align:middle line:90%
and bad luck befell the works.

00:49:48.160 --> 00:49:53.370 align:middle line:90%


00:49:53.370 --> 00:49:55.807 align:middle line:84%
The laborers walked
out, convinced

00:49:55.807 --> 00:49:57.765 align:middle line:84%
that the spirit of the
place had been offended.

00:49:57.765 --> 00:50:02.650 align:middle line:90%


00:50:02.650 --> 00:50:05.650 align:middle line:84%
To obtain forgiveness and
the spirit's goodwill,

00:50:05.650 --> 00:50:07.840 align:middle line:84%
the authorities decided
to build this monument.

00:50:07.840 --> 00:50:11.540 align:middle line:90%


00:50:11.540 --> 00:50:13.500 align:middle line:90%
[CYMBAL STRIKING]

00:50:13.500 --> 00:50:16.930 align:middle line:90%


00:50:16.930 --> 00:50:19.920 align:middle line:84%
>> The gesture must have been
appreciated by the supreme

00:50:19.920 --> 00:50:23.820 align:middle line:84%
powers, because straight away
work started again in the best

00:50:23.820 --> 00:50:26.980 align:middle line:90%
possible conditions.

00:50:26.980 --> 00:50:30.580 align:middle line:84%
It was deduced that the
mausoleum had great powers.

00:50:30.580 --> 00:50:33.280 align:middle line:84%
And today, people flock here
to bring offerings and pray

00:50:33.280 --> 00:50:35.467 align:middle line:90%
to Brahma.

00:50:35.467 --> 00:50:37.303 align:middle line:90%
[CYMBAL STRIKING]

00:50:37.303 --> 00:50:39.139 align:middle line:90%


00:50:39.139 --> 00:50:42.270 align:middle line:84%
>> Before concluding a
marriage, signing a contract,

00:50:42.270 --> 00:50:45.930 align:middle line:84%
or even buying a car, the
people of Thailand need to have

00:50:45.930 --> 00:50:48.080 align:middle line:84%
the ascent of the
spirits and the gods.

00:50:48.080 --> 00:50:52.690 align:middle line:90%


00:50:52.690 --> 00:50:55.180 align:middle line:90%
They make offerings to them.

00:50:55.180 --> 00:50:58.270 align:middle line:90%
They burn incense.

00:50:58.270 --> 00:51:01.780 align:middle line:84%
They offer lotus flowers,
garlands of jasmine.

00:51:01.780 --> 00:51:05.290 align:middle line:90%


00:51:05.290 --> 00:51:06.760 align:middle line:90%
They apply gold leaf.

00:51:06.760 --> 00:51:09.580 align:middle line:90%


00:51:09.580 --> 00:51:12.940 align:middle line:90%
They even set birds free.

00:51:12.940 --> 00:51:15.550 align:middle line:84%
Thus, they render
unto the gods the best

00:51:15.550 --> 00:51:17.320 align:middle line:90%
that the Earth has to offer.

00:51:17.320 --> 00:51:22.170 align:middle line:10%
[SPIRITUAL MUSIC PLAYING]

00:51:22.170 --> 00:52:13.000 align:middle line:90%